## 12. GATE OUTCOME TRACKER — Post-Market Settlement

### File: `live_monitoring/orchestrator/gate_outcome_tracker.py` (NEW — 247 lines)

| Method | When | What |
|--------|------|------|
| `log_signal()` | Every `should_fire()` call | Writes to `gate_signals_today.json` or `gate_blocked_today.json` |
| `settle_day()` | 16:05 ET (triggered after daily recap) | Fetches close prices via yfinance, calculates P&L in R-multiples, appends to `gate_outcomes.json`, archives daily files |
| `get_health(n)` | On-demand | Returns win rate, blocked/allowed ratio, avg R, streak from last N outcomes |

### Data Flow

```
should_fire()
  ↓
_log_result()
  ↓
log_signal() → gate_signals_today.json  (passed)
             → gate_blocked_today.json  (blocked)
  ↓
[16:05 ET]
settle_day() → yfinance close prices
             → P&L in R-multiples (default 1% stop)
             → gate_outcomes.json (append)
             → gate_signals_archive/YYYY-MM-DD.json
             → reset today files
  ↓
get_health(n=20) → { win_rate, blocked_vs_allowed, avg_r, streak }
```

### P&L Calculation
```
stop_distance = entry_price * 0.01  (1% default)
pnl_pct = (close - entry) / entry * 100  (LONG)
pnl_r = pnl_pct / 1.0  (R-multiple)
result = WIN if pnl_r > 0.5, LOSS if pnl_r < -0.5, NEUTRAL otherwise
```

